   <div class="entry-inner">
    <hr/>
    <center style="margin-top:15px;">
    </center>
    <center>
    </center>
    <p>
     <strong>
      Grand Utopia v1.20 ETS2
     </strong>
    </p>
    <hr/>
    <p>
     <strong>
      Changelog v1.20
     </strong>
     <br/>
     Main changes:
     <br/>
     – Map extension
     <br/>
     – Implementation of the “Utopic Markers” system
    </p>
    <p>
     <strong>
      Road network:
     </strong>
     <br/>
     – New interchange at Chaseville (created by Adyox), improving traffic flow toward future expansion to Elizabeth Island (UK)
     <br/>
     – Extension of the A3 motorway south of Eilmont
     <br/>
     – Addition of D34 and D341 roads
    </p>
    <p>
     <strong>
      Cities and villages:
     </strong>
     <br/>
     – Prat l’Étang added
     <br/>
     – Saint-Sébastien-le-Bec added
    </p>
    <p>
     <strong>
      Other changes:
     </strong>
     <br/>
     – Bug fixes and general error corrections
     <br/>
     – Adjustments to selected bus station prefabs
     <br/>
     – 7 new Utopic Markers added
     <br/>
     – Added cinematic camera point
     <br/>
     – 6 new artworks added
     <br/>
     The virtual world of Euro Truck Simulator 2 invites all truck fans to explore the new Grand Utopia map. It features a large network of roads, handcrafted cities, complex interchanges, and detailed natural environments.
    </p>
    <p>
     <strong>
      Standalone map
     </strong>
     <br/>
     Scale: 1:1
     <br/>
     – 49 cities
     <br/>
     – 199 companies
     <br/>
     – 22 truck dealers
     <br/>
     – Around 7500 km of roads
     <br/>
     – High level of detail
     <br/>
     – Balanced economy system
     <br/>
     – Configured traffic system
     <br/>
     – Requires all map DLCs to run
     <br/>
     – Built using standard assets for better optimization and low file size
    </p>
    <p>
     <strong>
      Changes:
     </strong>
     <br/>
     – Compatibility with ETS2 v1.45
     <br/>
     – Restoration of D5 road
     <br/>
     – Reconstruction of A1 backbone route
     <br/>
     – Updated map icon
     <br/>
     – Improvements near Perign and Career areas
     <br/>
     – Removed ferry on Château d’Ours island
     <br/>
     – Added highway markers
     <br/>
     – Added 2 landmarks
     <br/>
     – Added bus stops in Stellamar, Gerarme, Lossande-Zheles, Ba-Du-Shayen, Shato-D’Ur, La Josephine, Kurfayirak, Port Elvinka, Tour, Utopia-Portuera, Montsha-Soreng
     <br/>
     – Added bus icons for existing stops in Belmon, Granville, Riviera-Insas, Lelrotas, Alingsase, Laverne, Larzak, Pois Du-Nor, Jean-Du-Bartaile, Wil-Mari, Shavanny, Kenzi, Saint-Benois
     <br/>
     Launch: create a new profile and select the grandutopia.mbd module
    </p>
    <hr/>
    <strong>
     Credits:
    </strong>
    MyGodness
    <br/>
    <p style="margin-bottom:3px;">
    </p>
    <hr/>
    <hr>
    <strong>
     How to install ETS2 mods or ATS Mods
    </strong>
    <br/>
    In Euro Truck Simulator 2 it’s easy to install mods. You just need to download mod from here, copy/unzip files into: “My Documents\Euro Truck Simulator 2\mod” folder or if you play ATS please install mods to: “My Documents\American Truck Simulator\mod” folder. To unzip files you can use: WinRAR or 7zip. After that you need to activate the mods you want to use.
